        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 19 at 12:24PM CDT by NWS Corpus Christi TX</headline>
        <description>At 1223 PM CDT, the public reported strong thunderstorms along a line
extending from near Refugio to near Copano Village to 11 miles east
of Key Allegro. Movement was southwest at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Public.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Corpus Christi, Portland, Rockport, Sinton, Port Aransas, Taft,
Refugio, Woodsboro, Lamar, Ingleside, Aransas Pass, Gregory, St.
Paul, Ingleside On The Bay, Bayside, Quintana, Palm Harbor, Corpus
Christi North Beach, Key Allegro, and Copano Village.

This includes the following highways...
US Highway 181 between mile markers 614 and 644.
US Highway 183 between mile markers 664 and 668.
US Highway 77 between mile markers 610 and 650.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
